ing whether metadata will register for JDK, particularly regarding reachability metadata for Freemarker conditionals. My tests might generate agent metadata, which could include some reflection metadata for JDK. That could work, but I wonder if third-party metadata will lack JDK inclusion. Actually, the generated config might allow for reflective access to JDK in the test app. It's a bit convoluted, but I'm working through the details!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering reflection in tests**\\n\\nI'm wondering about using native reflection config generated in metadata. Since this is a test app, I might not need to rely on direct reflection for tests. It's true that Class.getName involves reflection, but the public API required by parse expects a fully qualified class name (FQCN) string. Also, I'll need to think about the inspect style since classes are public, but test methods are package-private. I'll use AssertJ and JUnit for writing the file, ensuring it's top-level public.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_7An0f4yvxesbj4cE8yi83fWd|fc_07d20810b13def180169f4b04893dc819191e651ad612a4ecf", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.freemarker/freemarker/2.3.31/src/test/java/fm/FreemarkerExtBeansMemberSelectorListMemberAccessPolicyInnerMemberSelectorTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage fm;\n\nimport freemarker.ext.beans.MemberSelectorListMemberAccessPolicy.MemberSelector;\nimport org.assertj.core.api.Assertions;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class FreemarkerExtBeansMemberSelectorListMemberAccessPolicyInnerMemberSelectorTest {\n\n    @Test\n    void parsesPublicFieldSelector() throws Exception {\n        String selector = FieldBackedBean.class.getName() + \".displayName\";\n\n        MemberSelector memberSelector = MemberSelector.parse(\n                selector,\n                FreemarkerExtBeansMemberSelectorListMemberAccessPolicyInnerMemberSelectorTest.class.getClassLoader());\n\n        Assertions.assertThat(memberSelector.getUpperBoundType()).isSameAs(FieldBackedBean.class);\n        Assertions.assertThat(memberSelector.getField()).isNotNull();\n        Assertions.assertThat(memberSelector.getField().getName()).isEqualTo(\"displayName\");\n        Assertions.assertThat(memberSelector.getMethod()).isNull();\n        Assertions.assertThat(memberSelector.getConstructor()).isNull();\n    }\n\n    public static class FieldBackedBean {\n        public String displayName;\n    }\n\n}\n"}, "partialJson": "{\"path\":\"tests/src/org.freemarker/freemarker/2.3.31/src/test/java/fm/FreemarkerExtBeansMemberSelectorListMemberAccessPolicyInnerMemberSelectorTest.java\",\"content\":\"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage fm;\\n\\nimport freemarker.ext.beans.MemberSelectorListMemberAccessPolicy.MemberSelector;\\nimport org.assertj.core.api.Assertions;\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\n\\npublic class FreemarkerExtBeansMemberSelectorListMemberAccessPolicyInnerMemberSelectorTest {\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void parsesPublicFieldSelector() throws Exception {\\n        String selector = FieldBackedBean.class.getName() + \\\".displayName\\\";\\n\\n        MemberSelector memberSelector = MemberSelector.parse(\\n                selector,\\n                FreemarkerExtBeansMemberSelectorListMemberAccessPolicyInnerMemberSelectorTest.class.getClassLoader());\\n\\n        Assertions.assertThat(memberSelector.getUpperBoundType()).isSameAs(FieldBackedBean.class);\\n        Assertions.assertThat(memberSelector.getField()).isNotNull();\\n        Assertions.assertThat(memberSelector.getField().getName()).isEqualTo(\\\"displayName\\\");\\n        Assertions.assertThat(memberSelector.getMethod()).isNull();\\n        Assertions.assertThat(memberSelector.getConstructor()).isNull();\\n    }\\n\\n    public static class FieldBackedBean {\\n        public String displayName;\\n    }\\n\\n}\\n\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 913, "output": 1163, "cacheRead": 14848, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 16924, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777643577963, "responseId": "resp_07d20810b13def180169f4b03a58988191bf866bf48ce97033"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_7An0f4yvxesbj4cE8yi83fWd|fc_07d20810b13def180169f4b04893dc819191e651ad612a4ecf", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 1314 bytes to tests/src/org.freemarker/freemarker/2.3.31/src/test/java/fm/FreemarkerExtBeansMemberSelectorListMemberAccessPolicyInnerMemberSelectorTest.java"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777643595334}]}
